commentPostTextItems.html: Crowd invades again and they run for their lives
A good performance by Pakistan while England were lack lustre today
The Anwar - Inzamam partnership, did put the match beyond reach and then Waqar struck early to peg England back into a defensive mood
Next game in this NatWest Series is Australia v Pakistan on Saturday
Please join us on Saturday at 9:45GMT or 10:45BST for Saturday's game

Match State: Pakistan won by 108 runs

stories.summary: The Pakistani gladiators Saeed Anwar (77) and Inzamam-ul-Haq (79) literally mauled England's bowling to raise Pakistan to an indomitable position for victory

stories.title: Pitch invasion should not detract from majestic Pakistan performance
stories.summary:
A partnership of 150 runs between Saeed Anwar and Inzamam-ul-Haq was the
foundation for a comfortable 108-run Pakistan win in the first game of the
2001 NatWest Series, though the moment of victory was delayed by a pitch
invasion from

stories.title: Pakistan heading for comfortable victory
stories.summary:
Penetrating bowling from Pakistan's seamers and the pressure of a large
target have resulted in the lights dimming on England's chances of winning
this game - even before the floodlights have come into effect

stories.title: Pakistan favourites at halfway stage
stories.summary: An innings of brutal power and subtle skill from Inzamam-ul-Haq has set up a challenging total for Pakistan to defend in this first NatWest Series encounter of 2001

stories.title: Pakistan get off to flying start
stories.summary: Saeed Anwar set the tone in the opening over, pulling Gough imperiously through mid-wicket for a boundary

stories.title: England lose Thorpe for ODI against Pakistan
stories.summary:
Pakistan have won the toss and chosen to bat in the first match of the
NatWest Series at Edgbaston amid cacophonous support for both sides
